      <exercise permid="Lru">
        <statement>
          <p permid="cLE">
            Can you distribute conjunctions over disjunctions?
            Disjunctions over conjunctions?
            Let's find out.
            Remember, two statements are logically equivalent if they are true in exactly the same cases.

            <ol permid="EpL">
              <li permid="zkt">
                <p permid="MLv">
                  Are the statements <m>P \vee (Q \and R)</m> and
                  <m>(P \vee Q) \and (P \vee R)</m> logically equivalent?
                  <solution permid="pXL">
                    Yes they are. We prove this by showing that their truth tables are identical:
                    \begin{center}
                    \begin{tabular}{c|c|c||c||c} <m>P</m> \amp <m>Q</m> \amp <m>R</m> \amp <m>P \vee (Q \and R)</m> \amp <m>(P \vee Q) \and (P \vee R)</m> \\ \hline
                    T \amp T \amp T \amp T \amp T\\
                    T \amp T \amp F \amp T \amp T \\
                    T \amp F \amp T \amp T \amp T \\
                    T \amp F \amp F \amp T \amp T \\
                    F \amp T \amp T \amp T \amp T \\
                    F \amp T \amp F \amp F \amp F \\
                    F \amp F \amp T \amp F \amp F \\
                    F \amp F \amp F \amp F \amp F
                    \end{tabular}
                    \end{center}
                  </solution>
                </p>
              </li>

              <li permid="frC">
                <p permid="sSE">
                  Are the statements <m>P \and (Q \vee R)</m> and
                  <m>(P \and Q) \vee (P \and R)</m> logically equivalent?
                  <solution permid="WeU">
                    It works again. Here are the two truth tables which prove it:
                    \begin{center}
                    \begin{tabular}{c|c|c||c||c} <m>P</m> \amp <m>Q</m> \amp <m>R</m> \amp <m>P \and (Q \vee R)</m> \amp <m>(P \and Q) \vee (P \and R)</m> \\ \hline
                    T \amp T \amp T \amp T \amp T\\
                    T \amp T \amp F \amp T \amp T \\
                    T \amp F \amp T \amp T \amp T \\
                    T \amp F \amp F \amp F \amp F \\
                    F \amp T \amp T \amp F \amp F \\
                    F \amp T \amp F \amp F \amp F \\
                    F \amp F \amp T \amp F \amp F \\
                    F \amp F \amp F \amp F \amp F
                    \end{tabular}
                    \end{center}
                  </solution>
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>

