          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution permid="fyG">
          <p permid="zUA">
            <m>A \cap B = \emptyset</m>.
            We know this because the set
            <m>A \cup B</m> contains 25 elements,
            each of which is either from <m>A</m> or from <m>B</m>,
            or from both.
            But there can't be any from both,
            because <m>9 + 16 = 25</m>.
            So <m>A \cap B</m> contains no elements - it is the empty set.
          </p>
        </solution>
