      <exercise permid="Hrv">
        <statement>
          <p permid="NCG">
            What does it mean for a function to be surjective?
            What does it mean to be injective.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution permid="LFP">
          <p permid="gbJ">
            A function is surjective if the codomain is equal to the range.
            A function is injective if every element of the codomain is the image (output) of at most one element from the domain.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>

